  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the prediction can help students better understand their own strengths and weaknesses as well as identify the areas they might benefit from extra assistance.",
    "Based on this, the term \"predicting student's academic performance\" refers to both predicting student's academic overall outcomes, as well as predicting students who can be at risk of fail or dropout or not graduating at planned time or even not meeting any educational goal (The Glossary of Educational Reform, 2013 at https://www.edglossary.org/professional-development/).",
    "The term \"student's academic overall outcomes\" describes a student's overall academic performance/achievement in a variety of courses throughout a specific period of time, such as a semester, year, or whole academic program.",
    "This reflects their knowledge of the concepts taught in these courses and the skills they cover.",
    "Typically, a range of evaluation techniques, such as exams, tests, essays, projects, and other assignments, are used to determine the overall academic performance and achievement Aljaloud et al (2022); Yang and Bai (2022)."
  ],
